<HEADLINE>
FT  21 DEC 93 / International Company News: Kells Minerals in reverse
takeover
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
World Fluids, the specialist chemical and additives manufacturer, is coming
to the market through its reverse takeover by Kells Minerals, the
Dublin-based exploration company.
Kells is paying Pounds 5.5m via the issue of 45.9m shares to Mr John and Ms
Geraldine Marett, giving them control. A further 3.58m shares are being
issued to the trustees of the World Fluids pension scheme for World Fluids'
principal property in Bury St Edmunds, Suffolk.
The name is to be changed to World Fluids (Holdings).
World Fluids, of which Mr John Marett is managing director, reported pre-tax
profits of Pounds 692,000 for the six months to September 30.
Kells' shares were suspended at 21p, up  1/2 p on the day.
</TEXT>
