</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   KIEV
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Ukraine announced yesterday that 17 of its 46 modern SS-24 strategic nuclear
weapons had been deactivated, Jill Barshay in Kiev and agencies report.
Mr Valery Shmarov, deputy prime minister, said the warheads had been moved
away from the launchers. 'We are prepared to remove all SS-24s from military
