FT  21 DEC 93 / Blast hits Lebanon party HQ
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BEIRUT
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A bomb exploded in the headquarters of Lebanon's largest Christian political
party yesterday and officials said there were several casualties, AP reports
from Beirut.
George Shahin, spokesman for the Phalange Party, said he saw the
headquarters go up in flames. Most of of the casualties occurred in the main
meeting hall.
