<HEADLINE>
FT  20 DEC 93 / World News in Brief: European Monetary System
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Dutch guilder remained the strongest currency in the system, alternating
throughout the week with the Irish punt for the top spot. Its disparity with
the Spanish peseta, the grid's weakest member, was some 4.58 per cent.
Currencies, Page 27
