<HEADLINE>
FT  18 DEC 93 / GM to pay back pick-up owners
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP-DJ
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   DETROIT
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A federal judge in Philadelphia has approved a legal settlement involving 6m
pick-up trucks made by General Motors between 1973 and 1987, AP-DJ reports
from Detroit. The settlement requires GM to give Dollars 1,000 coupons to
owners of GM pick-ups with side-mounted fuel tanks. The coupons can only be
used to buy GM trucks, most of which have profit margins greater than
Dollars 1,000. Analysts say the settlement will increase GM's profits.
Safety critics intend to appeal against the settlement, which covers 49
states. In Texas, a separate settlement was reached.
The settlements in Texas and in Philadelphia end more than 20 separate suits
seeking compensation for owners of GM pick-ups with side-mounted tanks. The
federal government says the pick-ups are more likely than comparable
vehicles to erupt in flames when hit from the side.
